# Rasm Rhino Bridge

Read `tools/rhino-bridge/README.md`, `tools/rhino-bridge/AGENTS.md`, and `.claude/skills/cs-testing/references/bridge-runtime.md`. Quality rails: `rasm-quality-operator.mdc`.

## Current Routes

| [INDEX] | [NEED]                    |
| :-----: | ------------------------- |
|   [1]   | Scenario runtime          |
|   [2]   | Project/source diagnostic |
|   [3]   | Bridge health             |
|   [4]   | Local API truth           |
|   [5]   | Yak flow                  |

[ROUTE]
- [1] `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge verify <scenario-or-glob>`
- [2] `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge check <target> [scenario]`
- [3] `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge doctor`
- [4] `uv run python -m tools.quality api doctor|resolve|query|show`
- [5] `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge package|deploy|publish rasm-bridge <version>`

## Runtime Rules

- Live Rhino bridge commands, bridge verify, bridge package live steps, and package staging use fail-fast leases.
- `bridge check <source.cs>` without a scenario can exit `3` after build succeeds and no runtime scenario is supplied.
- RhinoCode scenarios are diagnostics and verification, not publishing foundations.
- Use bridge-owned scenario routing, endpoint metadata, and `tools.quality` commands for all runtime proof.

## Scenario kit

- `rasm-bridge-scenarios.mdc` owns `*.verify.csx` authoring rules.
- `Rasm.TestKit.Scenarios` is staged automatically; no `#r`, `#load`, or absolute paths.
- The durable evidence is one batched `facts={json}` marker parsed by `BridgeMarker.Scan`.

## Static Rails

- Use `uv run python -m tools.quality static fix [paths...]` for managed cleanup.
- Use `uv run python -m tools.quality static build [paths...]` for managed compile/analyzer proof.
- Use `uv run python -m tools.quality test run [--target <csproj>]` for pure xUnit/CsCheck specs.
